statement.p: The graph below shows points on the function \displaystyle{y}={P}{\left({t}\right)}, which is periodic with a period of \displaystyle{T}={6}.
Find at least four different \displaystyle{t} values that are not shown on this graph, such that \displaystyle{P}{\left({t}\right)}={6}.
Give your answer as a list of numbers separated by commas, such as: \displaystyle-{5},-{2},{6},{9}
